<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-02-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-02-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="212" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d212">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Sampson</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-02-15"><hi rend="italic">February 15,
                                    1899</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 96.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Government of Ecuador has made
                            official proclamation of the suppression of the rebellion.</p>
                        <p>In the last battle over 600 were killed, several hundred mortally
                            wounded, and over 400 prisoners taken.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Archibald J.
                            Sampson.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>